FBIS4-60479 "drnes101_r_94002" FBIS-NES-94-101 Daily Report 25 May 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Work on Nuclear Reactors Suspended After Mishap Work on Nuclear Reactors Suspended After Mishap BK2505095894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0245 GMT 25 May 94 BK2505095894 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The Atomic Energy Regulatory Board, AERB, has ordered the suspension of all construction work of the inner container structures of the proposed nuclear reactors in Karnataka and Rajasthan. The AERB order was issued following preliminary analysis of the collapse of a large concrete portion of the inner container dome in the (Kaiga) unit-one project in Karnataka. The board has decided to review the construction procedure in use. The AERB chairman, Dr. A. Gopalakrishanan, has said that a high-level expert committee has been constituted to probe into the incident. He clarified that the (Kaiga) project is still under construction, and no nuclear fuel or heavy water has been transferred to the site. As such, there is no question of any radioactive release or radiological impact due to the incident, he added.
